        <scopecontent>
          <p>The Visual series includes photographs, negatives and slides, and two video cassettes in VHS format. Photographs, slides and negatives are divided into two major categories: Michigan Theater and Publicity. The Michigan Theater visual materials include images of the Theater, mostly after the restoration; photographs of Michigan leadership and staff, photographs taken during events and performances that took place at the theater; slides advertising local businesses and/or containing information about donors that were demonstrated before performances and during events. Among publicity images are studio photographs and slides advertising films and live performances at the Michigan Theater.</p>
          <p>One of the two VHS cassettes contains advertisement of the <title render="italic">1000 Airplanes on the Roof</title> performance at the Michigan Theater. The second VHS cassette contains a Canadian Broadcasting Corporation promotional video of <title render="italic">Mikado</title> at the Stratford Festival of Canada.</p>
